SEMDL Help Topic: reference split

Usage:
- `ssd split <input.ssd>`
- `ssd split <input.ssd> --dry-run`

Purpose:
- Separate Sidekick-eligible metadata into a paired Sidekick `.ssm` while preserving the Canvas skeleton in `.ssd`.
- `--dry-run` previews what stays in `.ssd` and what moves to `.ssm`.

Related help:
- `ssd help grammar`
- `ssd help samples`

Sample:
- `ssd split docs/examples/minimal.inline.ssd`
